│ THOUGHT: Now I understand the issue better. The assertion is checking that when we remove instructions inserted by the SCEV expander, those instructions should only be used by other instructions that were   │
│ also inserted during the same expansion. The crash suggests that there's a case where an instruction inserted by the expander is being used by something outside the inserted set, which violates this         │
│ assumption.                                                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Looking at the test case, the issue seems to be related to using `%iv.1` (a value from loop.1) in the trip count expression of loop.2 (`%ec.2 = icmp ult i64 %iv.2, %iv.1`). When vectorizing loop.2, the      │
│ vectorizer needs to expand the SCEV for the trip count, which involves `%iv.1`, but `%iv.1` is defined in a different loop and may not be properly handled in LCSSA form.                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
